    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A stereoscopic print or transparency in which a three-dimensional illusion is achieved through the use of alternating strips of images taken with a stereographic camera. The array of strips is covered by a grating that allows the right and left eye of the viewer the see only corresponding right or left image fragments, which creates the perceptual illusion of three dimensions. A stereoscopic print or transparency in which a three-dimensional illusion is achieved through the use of alternating strips of images taken with a stereographic camera. The array of strips is covered by a grating that allows the right and left eye of the viewer the see only corresponding right or left image fragments, which creates the perceptual illusion of three dimensions.</Note_Text>
